        },
        {
            "text": "Among bacterial :agents, Salmonella, S. aureus and LT-producing E. coli were the most frequent enteropathogens; the incidence of C. j e j u n i and Y. enterocolitica was found to be very low ( Table 2 ). Serogroup 09, biotype 2, lysotype X 3 was the unique isolated Y. enterocolitica strain.",
